---
import ServicePage from "../layouts/ServicePage.astro";
import PhoneLink from "../components/PhoneLink.astro";
import { SITE } from "../data/site";
---

<ServicePage
  title="Contact | Upper Cumberland Well Pump"
  description="Contact Upper Cumberland Well Pump — service requests, privacy and data questions, accessibility reports and provider inquiries for the Upper Cumberland, TN region."
  path="/contact/"
  h1="Contact Upper Cumberland Well Pump"
  crumbs={[
    { name: "Home", path: "/" },
    { name: "Contact", path: "/contact/" },
  ]}
  isService={false}
  defaultService="Not Sure"
  relatedLinks={[
    { label: "Request Service", href: "/request-service/" },
    { label: "About This Service", href: "/about-this-service/" },
    { label: "Privacy Policy", href: "/privacy-policy/" },
  ]}
>
  <p>
    The fastest path for a well problem is the request form on this page (or the full
    <a href="/request-service/">request-service form</a>) — it captures the details a provider needs
    and routes with the right priority. For everything else, here is how to reach the service:
  </p>

  <h2>By Phone</h2>
  <p>
    <PhoneLink prefix="Call " eventLabel="contact_phone_click" />
  </p>

  <h2>Service Requests</h2>
  <p>
    Use the <a href="/request-service/">request form</a>. Urgent no-water situations should go
    through the <a href="/emergency-no-water-well-service/">urgent no-water page</a> so they are flagged
    correctly.
  </p>

  <h2>Privacy and Data Requests</h2>
  <p>
    To ask what was stored about your submission or request its deletion, submit a note through the
    form on this page with "Privacy request" in the description, and include your lead reference
    number if you have it. See the <a href="/privacy-policy/">privacy policy</a> for details.
  </p>

  <h2>Accessibility Reports</h2>
  <p>
    Describe the barrier and the page it occurred on — details on the
    <a href="/accessibility/">accessibility page</a>. Reports are prioritized.
  </p>

  <h2>Local Providers</h2>
  <p>
    If you are a licensed well driller, pump installer or treatment installer serving the Upper
    Cumberland and want to receive referred requests, submit a note through the form with "Provider
    inquiry" in the description, including your license category and coverage area.
  </p>

  {
    SITE.email === "" && (
      <p class="fine-print">
        A public contact email address will be published here once available; until then, the form
        is the reliable channel.
      </p>
    )
  }
</ServicePage>
